COUNCILLOR Ngoako Setjie wants to know how it is that mayor John Mpe drives around in a car that is hired for R150 000 a month.Setjie, a DA councillor in the Capricorn Municipality in Limpopo, wants the public protector to investigate. Setjie said they can&rsquo;t just watch as money is misused and some communities do not even have drinkable water. &ldquo;Mayor John Mpe is using a new car and the municipality is still in the process of selling former mayor Gilbert Kganyago&rsquo;s car. &ldquo;The council is also planning to buy a new car for Mpe. &ldquo;This was never discussed during our council meetings,&rdquo; said Setjie.